## Overview
Create a reusable HTTP client service with built-in retry logic and exponential backoff.

## Implementation
```typescript
import { HttpClient, HttpClientRequest } from "@effect/platform"
import { Context, Effect, Layer, Schedule } from "effect"

// Error types
class HttpFetchError extends Schema.TaggedError<HttpFetchError>()(
  "HttpFetchError",
  { url: Schema.String, status: Schema.Number, message: Schema.String }
) {}

class RateLimitError extends Schema.TaggedError<RateLimitError>()(
  "RateLimitError",
  { url: Schema.String, retryAfter: Schema.Number }
) {}

// Service interface
class ScraperHttpClient extends Context.Tag("@geohints/ScraperHttpClient")<
  ScraperHttpClient,
  {
    readonly fetchPage: (url: string) => Effect.Effect<string, HttpFetchError | RateLimitError>
    readonly downloadImage: (url: string) => Effect.Effect<Uint8Array, HttpFetchError>
  }
>() {}
```

## Features
- Configurable retry policy (attempts, backoff factor)
- Request delay between requests (rate limiting)
- Custom User-Agent header
- Proper error mapping from platform errors

## References
- Current implementation: `fetchPage()` and `downloadImage()` in scrape-geomastr.ts
- Config: `config.requestDelay`, `config.userAgent`
